{
  "texts": [
    "We use the Python package Pillow [56] for RGB extraction.",
    "This simple approach achieves an F1 score of 0.93 when tested on 300 randomly sampled and manually annotated images.",
    "The primary cause of misclassifications arises when ChatGPT generates programming code-the edges of the code section displayed by ChatGPT share the same RGB values as the prompt section, which sometimes confuses our rule-based classification process.",
    "We address this problem on a rule basis in the text extraction step-since the text on the edge of codes is the only name of the language and \"Copy code, \" we can remove this section by a simple rule.Next, from the identified screenshots of ChatGPT, we extract prompts.",
    "We isolate the prompt section and apply Optical Character Recognition (OCR) using the Python package pytesseract [57]."
  ]
}